  "texts": [
    "At its core, OLS is nothing more than an algorithm that, when applied to a dataset, returns the coefficients β that minimize the sum of squared residuals.",
    "Econometrics clarifies what assumptions the researcher must believe about the underlying data generating process (DGP) to justify different interpretations of the algorithm's output.",
    "If we want to interpret β as the best linear unbiased estimator of the conditional expectation function, the Gauss-Markov theorem tells us what we need to be willing to assume (and defend) about the DGP.",
    "If we want to interpret β causally, we need to be willing to defend the conditional independence assumption.",
    "In this sense, econometrics provides empirical researchers with the terms of a contract: to endow an estimate with a particular interpretation, these are the assumptions you need to defend."
  ],
